</taxonomicName>
), sessile leaves with velutine to hispid indumentum (
<emphasis id="6C50543E379FB1DA5331D4FAB7E3ED42" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">vs.</emphasis>
at least the basal ones subpetiolate, sparsely hirsute to hirsute), broadly ovoid floral buds (
<emphasis id="E029ED017668E62C3221FF38D202949F" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">vs.</emphasis>
